"Here's the Python coding question:\n\n{\"title\": \"Maximum Sum of Subarray\", \"description\": \"Given an array of integers, find the maximum sum of a subarray within the given array.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef max_subarray_sum(arr: list) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list): A list of integers representing the input array.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the maximum sum of a subarray within the given array.\\n\", \"code\": \"\"\"\nimport itertools\n\ndef max_subarray_sum(arr: list) -> int:\n    # Initialize the maximum sum and the current sum\n    max_sum = float('-inf')\n    curr_sum = 0\n\n    # Iterate over all possible subarrays\n    for r in range(1, len(arr) + 1):\n        for subarr in itertools.combinations_with_replacement(arr, r):\n            # Calculate the sum of the current subarray\n            curr_sum = sum(subarr)\n\n            # Update the maximum sum if necessary\n            max_sum = max(max_sum, curr_sum)\n\n    return max_sum\n\n\"\"\", \"tests\": [\"assert max_subarray_sum([-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4]) == 6\", \"assert max_subarray_sum([1]))] == 1\", \"assert max_subarray_sum([5,-7,3,5]) == 8\", \"assert max_subarray_sum([-1, 0, 1, 2, -1, -4]) == 6\"]}"